headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had 22 points, 11 assists and eight rebounds, P.J. Washington scored 13 of his 16 points in the fourth quarter and the Charlotte Hornets defeated the Atlanta Hawks 116-106 on Wednesday night for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball scores 22, Hornets pull away late to beat Hawks 116-106

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 35 points and 17 rebounds, James Harden scored 21 points and added 11 assists, and the Philadelphia 76ers edged the Cleveland Cavaliers 118-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has 35 points, 17 rebounds as 76ers beat Cavs 118-114

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 29 points and 13 rebounds in an efficient 26-minute performance to help the Denver Nuggets cruise to a 127-109 victory over the struggling Washington Wizards on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic shines, Nuggets cruise to 127-109 victory over Wizards

headlines.description: — Spencer Dinwiddie knows it's up to Luka Doncic whether he takes the last shot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dinwiddie hits 3 at buzzer, Mavericks beat Nets 113-111

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 31 points, Julius Randle added 20 points and nine rebounds, and the New York Knicks beat the Portland Trail Blazers 128-98 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: RJ Barrett scores 31, Knicks beat Trail Blazers by 30

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 36 points, Mikal Bridges added 26 and the NBA-leading Phoenix Suns beat the Houston Rockets 129-112 on Wednesday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker has 36 points, NBA-leading Suns beat Rockets 129-112

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — The Minnesota Timberwolves have been gobbling up wins against struggling teams, including this one against the uncharacteristically reeling Los Angeles Lakers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Timberwolves pull away to beat reeling Lakers 124-104

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray had 26 points and 12 assists and the San Antonio Spurs held on to beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 122-120 on Wednesday night, snapping a two-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs fend off Thunder 122-120 to end 2-game slide

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell tries to keep his cool with the officials.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 25 of 37 points in 3rd, Jazz beat Bulls

events.name: Boston Celtics at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry went down with a left foot injury late in the first half and Golden State coach Steve Kerr didn't like Marcus Smart's lunging move at the reigning NBA scoring champ.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry injures left foot in Warriors blowout loss to Celtics

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 36 points and 10 rebounds, Wesley Matthews made a clutch 3-pointer with 1:32 remaining, and the Milwaukee Bucks held off the Sacramento Kings 135-126 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 36 points, Bucks hold off Kings 135-126

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 31 points and the streaking Toronto Raptors held off a fourth-quarter comeback by the Los Angeles Clippers for a 103-100 victory Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam, Raptors beat Clippers to extend winning streak to 5
